# CreatorForge - Cursor Rules

## Project Context
CreatorForge is a free, AI-powered YouTube creator toolkit built with Next.js 14 (App Router), TypeScript, Tailwind CSS, and Supabase. The app supports 9 languages (en, it, es, de, fr, pt, ru, ja, zh) via next-intl.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 14 with App Router
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui components
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Storage)
- **AI**: Groq API (free tier) with OpenAI SDK
- **i18n**: next-intl
- **Forms**: react-hook-form + zod
- **Icons**: lucide-react

## Code Style Rules
- Use functional components with TypeScript
- Use Server Components by default, Client Components only when needed ('use client')
- All UI components use shadcn/ui pattern with cva for variants
- Use '@/...' import alias for all imports
- All new pages go in app/[locale]/... structure
- All translations go in messages/{locale}.json files
- Use cn() utility from @/lib/utils for className merging
- Prefer Server Actions over API routes for mutations
- Always handle loading and error states
- Use Suspense for data fetching

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., DashboardCard.tsx)
- Utilities: camelCase (e.g., formatNumber.ts)
- Pages: page.tsx (Next.js convention)
- Layouts: layout.tsx (Next.js convention)

## Multi-language Rules
- NEVER hardcode text in components
- ALWAYS use useTranslations() hook
- Add new strings to ALL 9 language files (en, it, es, de, fr, pt, ru, ja, zh)
- Use descriptive keys (e.g., "dashboard.welcome", not "text1")

## Free Tier Constraints
- YouTube API: 10K units/day - use caching aggressively
- Groq AI: ~30K requests/day - implement rate limiting (10/user/day)
- Supabase: 500MB DB - optimize queries, cleanup old data
- Always consider cost when implementing features

## Architecture Principles
- Keep components small and focused (<150 lines)
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks
- Use Server Components for data fetching
- Cache API responses in Supabase or Upstash Redis
- Implement proper error boundaries

## When Writing Code
- Always add TypeScript types (no 'any')
- Include JSDoc comments for public functions
- Handle all edge cases (loading, error, empty states)
- Add accessibility attributes (aria-*, role)
- Make components responsive (mobile-first)
- Use dark mode compatible colors

## Do NOT
- Use 'any' type
- Hardcode strings (use translations)
- Create API routes when Server Actions work
- Skip error handling
- Use inline styles (use Tailwind)
- Import from node_modules directly in components
"@ | Out-File -FilePath ".cursorrules" -Encoding utf8